BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Garden Sculpture Workshop with Artist Larry Bechtel - Part I
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260315T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260315T153000
UID:10001952-1773579600-1773588600@www.taubmanmuseum.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hero-events.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Does your garden\, yard\, or window box need a little surprise
 \, something to peek out from under your flowers and bring a smile to anyb
 ody who comes by?\n\nIf so\, we invite you to sign up for Larry Bechtel
 ’s newest sculpture class and make a concrete garden face (about 6″ hi
 gh and 4-5″ inches wide)!\n\nThis will be a fun project\, but you will a
 lso learn three sculpting skills: modeling a face in clay\, molding this i
 n plaster\, and casting a concrete copy from the plaster mold.\n\nNo exper
 ience is necessary. All materials will be provided.\n\nPlease note that sa
 mples pictured are only for inspiration – individual class projects will
  vary depending on students’ creative visions.\n\nTwo sessions are inclu
 ded for the price of one!\n\nPART I – Sunday\, March 15\, 1-3:30 PM\n\nP
 ART II – Sunday\, March 22\, 1-3:30 PM\n\nPrice for both sessions: Membe
 rs: $150 | General Public: $175\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/g
 arden-sculpture-workshop-2026
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/garden-sculpture-workshop-2026
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spring Break Mini-Camp
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T123000
UID:10001949-1774085400-1774096200@www.taubmanmuseum.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hero-events.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Let’s celebrate Spring Break with a fun morning creating art
 !\n\nThe theme of this one-day mini-camp will be centered around books.\n\
 nInspired by our latest exhibition\, LeUyen Came Along: The Art of LeUyen 
 Pham \, participants will learn about the illustrative art and books that 
 LeUyen has created in her long career.\n\nSome classics you may recognize 
 include “Vampirina Ballerina\,” “The Princess in Black\,” and “I
 tty-Bitty Kitty-Corn\,” and more!\n\nChildren will get to create everyth
 ing from a bookmark and collage to their very own book.\n\nThis camp is fo
 r children kindergarten through fifth grade.\n\nRegistration required.\n\n
 Members: $60 | General Public: $75\n\nNot a member? Join today for discoun
 ts on camps and classes\, exclusive invites\, free reciprocal admission to
  the Virginia Museum of Fine Arts in Richmond\, and more. Click here to le
 arn more and become a member.\n\nAlong Came LeUyen: The Art of LeUyen Pham
  was organized by the National Center for Children’s Illustrated Literat
 ure\, Abilene\, Texas.\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/event/spri
 ng-break-mini-camp/
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/event/spring-break-mini-camp/
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Garden Sculpture Workshop with Artist Larry Bechtel - Part II
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260322T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260322T153000
UID:10001953-1774184400-1774193400@www.taubmanmuseum.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hero-events.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Does your garden\, yard\, or window box need a little surprise
 \, something to peek out from under your flowers and bring a smile to anyb
 ody who comes by?\n\nIf so\, we invite you to sign up for Larry Bechtel
 ’s newest sculpture class and make a concrete garden face (about 6″ hi
 gh and 4-5″ inches wide)!\n\nThis will be a fun project\, but you will a
 lso learn three sculpting skills: modeling a face in clay\, molding this i
 n plaster\, and casting a concrete copy from the plaster mold.\n\nNo exper
 ience is necessary. All materials will be provided.\n\nPlease note that sa
 mples pictured are only for inspiration – individual class projects will
  vary depending on students’ creative visions.\n\nTwo sessions are inclu
 ded for the price of one!\n\nPART I – Sunday\, March 15\, 1-3:30 PM\n\nP
 ART II – Sunday\, March 22\, 1-3:30 PM\n\nPrice for both sessions: Membe
 rs: $150 | General Public: $175\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/e
