BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mixed Media Face Cards Class
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T123000
UID:10001956-1774693800-1774701000@www.taubmanmuseum.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hero-events.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Turn ordinary playing cards into extraordinary miniature artwo
 rks in this creative mixed-media class!\n\nUsing face cards as your canvas
 \, you’ll design and embellish a one-of-a-kind keepsake inspired by eith
 er a beach or garden theme.\n\nLearn how to layer “bits and bobs” like
  beads\, ribbon\, wire\, charms\, and tiny miniatures to add texture\, dim
 ension\, and personality to your piece.\n\nLeave with a beautifully finish
 ed keepsake ready to hang or display\, and the skills to create more at ho
 me!\n\nPlease note that the sample image shows examples of cards created b
 y the instructor. Cards created in class will differ in style and theme.\n
 \nRegistration required.\n\nMembers: $20 | General Public: $25\n\nNot a Me
 mber? Join today and receive discounts on classes and camps\, exclusive in
 vites to events\, and FREE reciprocal membership to the Virginia Museum of
  Fine Arts in Richmond\, among other perks! Click here to learn more and j
 oin.\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/mixed-media-playing-cards
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/mixed-media-playing-cards
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Material and Light: A Conversation with Artist Nancy Lorenz
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T150000
UID:10001957-1774706400-1774710000@www.taubmanmuseum.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hero-events.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Get an extra special sneak peek at an upcoming exhibition with
  artist Nancy Lorenz in advance of her solo exhibition\, The Elements \,
  opening February 2027 here at the Taubman Museum of Art.\n\nIn conversati
 on with Curator Laura K. Higgins\, Lorenz will explore her distinctive p
 ractice\, which draws on a lifetime of engagement with rich materials and 
 surface techniques.\n\nLorenz’s luminous works—layered with gold\, sil
 ver\, and palladium leaf\, mother-of-pearl inlay\, resin\, and lacquer—r
 eflect both Western abstraction and deep influence from traditional Japane
 se craft and aesthetics\, a sensibility first seeded during her formative 
 years in Tokyo.\n\nPresented in dialogue with selections of Japanese print
 s and a kimono from the Museum’s Sharing Collection\, this program situa
 tes Lorenz’s material language within broader artistic and cultural lin
 eages\, offering insight into the ideas and influences that will shape her
  forthcoming exhibition.\n\nMembers Free | General Public: $8\n\nNot a Mem
 ber? Join today and receive benefits such as discounts on classes and camp
 s\, invitations to exclusive events\, free reciprocal membership to the Vi
 rginia Museum of Fine Arts in Richmond\, and more! Click here to learn mor
 e.\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/conversation-with-nancy-lorenz
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/conversation-with-nancy-lorenz
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Architectural Highlights Behind-the-Scenes Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T193000
UID:10001942-1775239200-1775244600@www.taubmanmuseum.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hero-events.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Discover the Taubman Museum of Art from a whole new perspectiv
 e during this Architectural Highlights Tour\, an engaging\, behind-the-sce
 nes experience that reveals the vision\, innovation\, and craftsmanship be
 hind one of Roanoke’s most iconic landmarks that Architectural Digest na
 med one of the best designed museums in the nation.\n\nLed in collaboratio
 n with local architects and individuals directly involved in the creation 
 of the building\, this approximately 90-minute guided tour traces the Muse
 um’s architectural story from the ground up.\n\nDesigned by Randall Stou
 t and inspired by the natural forms of Virginia’s landscape\, the buildi
 ng’s soaring glass\, steel\, patinated zinc\, and locally sourced Hokie 
 Stone come alive through expert insight and little-known details.\n\nAlong
  the way\, guests will explore dramatic interior spaces\, flexible perform
 ance and gallery areas\, the “Vault” where artworks not on view are st
 ored\, and the sophisticated systems that protect the Museum’s art while
  welcoming the community.\n\nThe tour culminates at the Top of the Taubman
  Balcony\, where sweeping views of downtown Roanoke\, the railroad corrido
 r\, and surrounding landmarks provide a fitting finale. Guests are invited
  to raise a glass during a celebratory champagne toast to cap off this spe
 cial experience.\n\nWhether you’re a design enthusiast\, architecture pr
 ofessional\, or curious local\, this special tour offers rare access\, com
 pelling stories\, and a memorable way to experience the Taubman Museum of 
 Art.\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/arch-tour-april-3
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/arch-tour-april-3
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
